column1: #Text=—A congregation was this day holden for granting degrees, &c, w hen the following were conferred:— Bachelor of Divinity—Rev.
#Text=Pears, of Corpus Christi College: John M.
#Text=Charles Seager, Worcester College; Edward MLeod, ditto ; Rev.
#Text=Dixon, Trinity College; Borlase Adams, Exeter College; John M.
#Text=The Boden Professor of Sanscrip has given notice that he will continue his lectures on Tuesdays and Thursdays during this term, to commence May 2, at a (piarter before ten oclock.
#Text=The Professpr of Moral Philosophy will continue his lectures on the Republic of Plato, on Tuesdays and Thursdays.
#Text=The Professor of Botany intends to begin a course of lectures on Monday, the 29th instant, at twooek-ck, and continue them on the alternate week days.
